   Actually, layer ordering in Axum: outer layers are added LAST (bottom-up). The current code has:
   ```rust
   .layer(GovernorLayer { ... })  // applied second
   .layer(cors)                    // applied first (outermost)
   ```
   Wait no -- in Axum, layers wrap from bottom to top. The LAST .layer() call wraps the outermost. Let me re-read the current code:
   ```rust
   public_router
       .merge(protected_router)
       .layer(GovernorLayer { ... })  // wraps merged result
       .layer(cors)                    // wraps everything (outermost)
